name: The Taj
description: The Taj Mahal, incorporates and expands on the design traditions of Indo-Islamic and earlier Mughal architecture. It designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1983 for being "the jewel of Muslim art in India and one of the universally admired masterpieces of the world's heritage". It is regarded as a symbol of India's rich history. On an average Taj Mahal attracts 7–8 million visitors per year.
